      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "INCLINATION (8) was well supported last time and rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but had to settle for the minor money, finishing a one length second (29.87) over 515m at Sandown. Didn't win last time but still ran one of the quickest times on the card. Makes plenty of appeal. PAW GORDY (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing sixth (22.34) last time in a Special conditions H at Ballarat. Form here at the trip sound including four wins. Form from his last run is proving strong. Worth another chance. SIR DODGE (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (30.56) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Has a good record at this journey. Solid formlines coming through his last run. Cannot be left out. MORNING (7) cannot be overlooked following a recent top-three finish.",
